      <h1>Career Timeline</h1>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-4">
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>1991:</strong> Selected for the Indian Police Service (IPS) and began training at the National Police Academy in Hyderabad.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>October 1992 - October 1994:</strong> Served as Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) in Warangal (Rural), where he launched the "Jana Jaagruti" public awareness campaign.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>November 1994 - February 1995:</strong> Transferred to Pulivendula as ASP, where he focused on curbing anti-social elements.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>February 1995 onwards:</strong> Returned to Warangal as Officer on Special Duty (OSD).</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>June 1995 - June 1997:</strong> Promoted to Superintendent of Police (SP) and posted to Cuddapah district. He was instrumental in restoring order and became known as the "Cuddapah Tiger".</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>June 1997 - April 1998:</strong> Served as SP of Karimnagar district, where he continued his anti-Naxalite operations.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>November 1998 - September 1999:</strong> Promoted to Assistant Inspector General (AIG) for Welfare and Sports, with an additional charge of computers.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>September 4, 1999:</strong> Assassinated in Hyderabad.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>September 4, 2000:</strong> A statue was unveiled in his honor at Sanjiva Reddy Nagar Cross Roads, Hyderabad.</li>
      </ul>
